dex.php |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215221220/http://www.ligo.org/science/Publication-GW150914Astro/index.php |archivedate=2016-02-15 |publisher=LIGO Scientific Collaboration |accessdate=2016-02-13 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>信號名稱'''GW150914'''的意義為「重力波2015年9月14日」，GW是重力波"Gravitational Wave"，150914是發現日期。<ref name="PRL-20160211" /><ref name="Naeye"/>

对于引力波的实验探寻已经超过了50年。其与物质间的作用十分微弱，以致爱因斯坦本人都怀疑其是否能被探测到。此次探测到的引力波所造成的时空变化相对于LIGO探测器的一个干涉臂而言，相当于头发丝的宽度之于地球与太阳外最近恒星的距离。然而在併合最后阶段，等价于约3倍[[太阳质量|太阳质量]]的能量在不到1秒的时间内以引力波的形式释出，瞬时功率非常巨大，大于[[可观测宇宙|可观测宇宙]]中所有星体发光功率总和。<ref name="Nature_11Feb16"/><ref name="DetectionScienceSummary"/><ref name = "CBS2016-02-11"/><ref>{{cite web |language=en |title=Found! Gravitational Waves, or a Wrinkle in Spacetime |work=National Geographic News |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2016/02/160211-gravitational-waves-found-spacetime-science/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160212083049/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2016/02/160211-gravitational-waves-found-spacetime-science/ |archivedate=2016-02-12 |accessdate=2016-02-12 |last=Drake |first=N. |date=2016-02-11 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

此次探测验证了广义相对论最后一项未被证实的理论预测，同时开启了[[引力波天文学|引力波天文学]]的新纪元。[[引力波|引力波]]就此作为一种粒子和电磁波之外的新的探针，将被用于探测过去未能探测到的天体现象，如中子星的诞生、演化以及[[引力坍缩|衰亡]]以及宇宙诞生之初的图景。<ref name="PRL-20160211" /><ref name="tests" /><ref name="astrophysics" /><ref name="CNN-A">{{cite news|language=en|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/02/12/opinions/gravity-wave-team-conversation/|title=How we made the gravitational wave discovery|first=M.|last=Hendry|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2016-02-17|archive-date=2016-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306050421/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/02/12/opinions/gravity-wave-team-conversation/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="BBC-A">{{cite news|language=en|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-35524440|title=Einstein's gravitational waves 'seen' from black holes|first=P.|last=Ghosh|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2016-02-17|archive-date=2016-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160212222326/http://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-35524440|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=en |title=What happens when LIGO texts you to say it’s detected one of Einstein’s predicted gravitational waves |first=C. |last=Hanna |date=2016-02-11 |work=National Post |archivedate=2016-02-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215104303/http://news.nationalpost.com/news/world/what-happens-when-ligo-texts-you-to-say-its-detected-one-of-einsteins-predicted-gravitational-waves |url=http://news.nationalpost.com/news/world/what-happens-when-ligo-texts-you-to-say-its-detected-one-of-einsteins-predicted-gravitational-waves |accessdate=2016-02-14 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

